of the temperature of the regions of the<lb/>
Atmosphere, into which they are<lb/>
elevated. - And in all latitudes,<lb/>
when above 15,000 feet high, they<lb/>
are covered with constant <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">ice</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">snow</add>, -<lb/>
