perpetual Snow. -<lb/>
- The tendency of Mountains is<lb/>
necessarily to diminish the heat of the<lb/>
Countries in which they exist, |_ &amp;<lb/>
they are found most elevated, &amp;<lb/>
upon the greatest scale in those<lb/>
regions, in which such effect must<lb/>
be most beneficial. -<lb/>
